## Formula Summary

| Property                 | Value              |
| ------------------------ | ------------------ |
| Formula Type             | Laundry Pod Liquid |
| Total Surfactant Content | 66%                |
| Enzyme System            | Included           |
| Polymer System           | Sokalan HP20       |
| Solvent System           | PG + Glycerin      |
| Neutralization Agent     | MEA                |
| pH Adjuster              | Citric Acid        |

---

## Ingredient Functions

| Ingredient         | Function                             |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------ |
| LAS 96             | Primary anionic surfactant           |
| SLES               | Foaming and detergency               |
| AO 7               | Nonionic cleaning booster            |
| AO 9               | Grease removal                       |
| XL 80              | Low-temperature cleaning performance |
| Coconut Fatty Acid | Soap formation after neutralization  |
| MEA                | Neutralization and pH control        |
| Sokalan HP20       | Soil release and anti-redeposition   |
| Enzymes            | Protein and starch stain removal     |
| Fragrance          | Consumer sensory profile             |
| Citric Acid        | Final pH adjustment                  |

---

## Manufacturing Notes

1. Add solvents (PG and Glycerin).
2. Add nonionic surfactants under agitation.
3. Slowly add LAS.
4. Neutralize LAS and fatty acid with MEA.
5. Add polymer.
6. Cool below 30°C.
7. Add enzymes.
8. Add fragrance and color.
9. Final pH adjustment using citric acid solution.
10. Fill into PVA film and seal.

